snippet.title: High Court told Johnny Depp’s lawyers have video showing Amber Heard ‘attacked’ sister
snippet.description:
Subscribe to the Evening Standard on YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC7RQon_YwCnp_LbPtEwW65w?sub_confirmation=1

Actress Amber Heard today faced a bombshell new claim that she had been violent towards own sister, after a video emerged said to show bruises from the alleged attack.

The star’s younger sister Whitney Henriquez told the High Court yesterday she had seen Heard punch Johnny Depp in the face but insisted it was a defensive action against the out-of-control actor.

She insisted she was not “frightened” of Heard, and denied ever being on the receiving end of any violence.

This morning, Depp’s lawyer David Sherborne accused Ms Henriquez of lying and said his team had received a video overnight which they say undermines her evidence.

Read more: https://www.standard.co.uk/news/uk/amber-heard-violence-sister-johnny-depp-a4507471.html
